Agrokor May Offer 230 Euros for Mercator Share, Finance Says

-- B y   B o r i s   C e r n i
-- 
2011-03-09T07:43:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-09/agrokor-may-offer-230-euros-for-mercator-share-finance-says.html
Agrokor d.d. will probably bid for a
stake in  Slovenia ’s  Mercator Poslovni Sistem (MELR)  d.d. today and
offer as much as 230 euros ($320) per share, Finance  reported ,
without saying where it got the information.    Pivovarna Lasko (PILR)  Group d.d. is selling a 23.3 percent stake
to help cut debt, the Ljubljana-based newspaper said.  Agrokor, Croatia’s biggest privately held group, said Feb.
18 it’s considering a bid for the Slovenian retailer, which in
turn expressed interest in acquiring Agrokor’s Croatian retail
chain Konzum d.d.  Mercator shares closed at 161 euros yesterday on the
Ljubljana stock exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Boris Cerni in Ljubljana, Slovenia, at 
 bcerni@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  